<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Personal Details</title>
</head>
<body>

    <h1><u>Personal Details</u></h1>

    <p><b>Name:</b> Arafat Momin</p>
    <p><b>Age:</b> 18</p>
    <p><b>Course:</b> <i>Computer Science and Engineering</i></p>
    <p><b>College:</b> <u>Your College Name</u></p>
    <p><b>City:</b> Sangli</p>
    <p><b>Hobby:</b> <mark>Playing Cricket</mark></p>

</body>
</html>





 
Code explanation (line by line)
•	<!DOCTYPE html>
Tells the browser that this is an HTML5 document. 
•	<html>
This is the root tag. All HTML code comes inside it. 
•	<head>
Contains information about the page, not the visible content. 
•	<title>Personal Details</title>
This sets the title shown on the browser tab. 
•	<body>
Everything inside the body is visible on the webpage. 
•	<h1><u>Personal Details</u></h1>
h1 creates a main heading.
u underlines the text. 
•	<p><b>Name:</b> Arafat Momin</p>
p creates a paragraph.
b makes “Name:” bold. 
•	<i>Computer Science and Engineering</i>
i displays text in italic. 
•	<mark>Playing Cricket</mark>
mark highlights the text. 
•	</body> and </html>
These are closing tags. 
________________________________________
Simple viva explanation in one go
If teacher says “Explain your program,” you can say:
“This program creates a simple HTML page to display personal details. I used formatting tags like bold, italic, underline, and mark. The title appears on the browser tab, and all personal information is displayed inside the body section.”
