Common viva questions
1. What is HTML?
HTML stands for HyperText Markup Language. It is used to create web pages.
2. What is the use of <!DOCTYPE html>?
It tells the browser that the document is an HTML5 document.
3. What is the difference between <head> and <body>?
•	<head> contains page information like title. 
•	<body> contains visible content. 
4. What does <title> do?
It displays the page title on the browser tab.
5. What is the use of <p> tag?
It creates a paragraph.
6. What does <b> tag do?
It makes text bold.
7. What does <i> tag do?
It makes text italic.
8. What does <u> tag do?
It underlines the text.
9. What does <mark> tag do?
It highlights the text.
10. What are opening and closing tags?
Example: <p> is opening tag and </p> is closing tag.
________________________________________
One practical tip
If the teacher asks “Why did you use formatting tags?”, say:
“Formatting tags make the text more clear, attractive, and easy to read.”

